"title": "4963: past, the",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4963: past, the",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ transforms the past and sets people free to live in a new way. God's people should remember former blessings but not return to former sins.</p>\n<h2>Recalling God's work in the past</h2>\n<h3>Remembering God's work of creation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:11\">EXO 20:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:5-Ps104:9\">PSA 104:5–104:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:1-Ps136:9\">PSA 136:1–136:9</a></p>\n<h3>Remembering God's saving works</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:5\">PSA 105:5</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:12\">1CH 16:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:2\">DEU 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:2\">JOS 24:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:6\">1SA 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:7\">NEH 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:6\">PSA 106:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps114:1\">PSA 114:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:10\">PSA 136:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:5\">PSA 143:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:1-Isa51:2\">ISA 51:1–51:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:5\">MIC 6:5</a></p>\n<h3>Remembering God's work in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:8\">2TI 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:26\">1CO 11:23–11:26</a> <em>One of the purposes of the Lord's Supper is to remember Jesus Christ and his death on the cross.</em></p>\n<h2>Learning from the past</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:4\">ROM 15:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:9\">DEU 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:7\">DEU 32:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:4\">ZEC 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:6\">1CO 10:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:11\">1CO 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:16\">HEB 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:5-1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:5–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:12\">1JN 3:12</a></p>\n<h2>Rediscovering God's word from the past</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:8-2Kgs22:13\">2KI 22:8–22:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:15-2Chr34:21\">2CH 34:15–34:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:1-2Kgs23:3\">2KI 23:1–23:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:29-2Chr34:31\">2CH 34:29–34:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:21-2Kgs23:23\">2KI 23:21–23:23</a></p>\n<h2>Leaving the past behind</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ sets believers free from the past</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:17\">2CO 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:16\">ISA 65:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:3-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:3–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13-Col1:14\">COL 1:13–1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Warnings not to rely on or be preoccupied with the past</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:18\">ISA 43:18</a></strong> <em>This can mean either that God is not to be restricted to his past actions or that Israel should forget their former sins.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:13-Phil3:14\">PHP 3:13–3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Dangers of the past</h2>\n<h3>The danger of ignoring the past</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:11\">PSA 78:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:8\">EXO 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:18\">DEU 32:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:13\">PSA 106:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:21\">PSA 106:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:13\">HOS 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>The danger of lapsing into past sins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:8-Gal4:9\">GAL 4:8–4:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:4-Heb6:6\">HEB 6:4–6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:9\">2PE 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:4-Rev2:5\">REV 2:4–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:3\">REV 3:3</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ supersedes God's revelation in the past</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ supersedes earlier expectations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:30\">ACT 17:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:15-Acts14:16\">ACT 14:15–14:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ supersedes earlier covenants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:22\">HEB 7:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:2\">HEB 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:13\">HEB 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14-Heb9:15\">HEB 9:14–9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:15-Heb10:18\">HEB 10:15–10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33-Jer31:34\">JER 31:33–31:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:24\">HEB 12:24</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ reveals God's past mystery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:26-Col1:27\">COL 1:26–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:25-Rom16:26\">ROM 16:25–16:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:7\">1CO 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9\">EPH 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:2-Eph3:6\">EPH 3:2–3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:9\">EPH 3:9</a></p>",
